snippet: Paddle8, a four-year-old start-up with big-name backers, plans to announce on Wednesday that it has raised $34 million in a new round of financing.

byline.original: By MICHAEL J. de la MERCED

abstract: Online auction house Paddle8 is expected to announce it has raised $34 million in latest round of financing, setting stage for start-up to expand its online auction services worldwide; company seeks to be lower-priced competitor to auction houses like Sotheby's and Christie's.
lead_paragraph: Paddle8, a four-year-old start-up with big-name backers, plans to announce on Wednesday that it has raised $34 million in a new round of financing.

headline.print_headline: Online Auction House Aims to Give Big Players a Run for Their Money
headline.main: Online Auction House Aims to Give Big Houses a Run for Their Money
